#. type: Plain text
#: origin/root-privileges.txt:7
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"SYNOPSIS:\n"
"\tHow to prevent file deletion/modification, even from root.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/root-privileges.txt:9
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"HINT:\n"
"===========================================================================\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/root-privileges.txt:15
msgid ""
"Ed. note: as an unknown person explained: \"I was reading the lfs-hints and "
"I came across the root-priveleges hint. I am not sure if this is what was "
"intended by the hint, but it sounds as if any user can set this attr to a "
"file and thereby prevent root from being able to change/delete, etc."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/root-privileges.txt:19
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"That is not *quite* true. The superuser has to be the one to set and "
"remove\n"
"the bit from a file. Once superuser sets this bit, then yes it is "
"basically\n"
"unchangeable unless the bit is removed.\"\n"
"===========================================================================\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/root-privileges.txt:22
msgid "A less-known feature of the ext2 filesystem:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/root-privileges.txt:24
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"  you can set a file to not be changable by anyone including root, like "
"so:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/root-privileges.txt:26
#, no-wrap
msgid "        chattr +i somefile.txt\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/root-privileges.txt:28
#, no-wrap
msgid "  this can be undone via the command:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/root-privileges.txt:30
#, no-wrap
msgid "        chattr -i somefile.txt\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/root-privileges.txt:33
msgid ""
"Like this even root can't delete this file. See man chattr for more "
"information."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/root-privileges.txt:36
msgid ""
"e.g.: chattr +i -R /usr/lib would recursively change attributes of "
"directories and their contents."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/root-privileges.txt:37
msgid "Source: http://bastille-linux.sourceforge.net/faq.html"
msgstr ""
